fields.title: Introduction to Software Testing
fields.description: This course provides a solid foundation in software testing principles, tools, and practices. You will learn different testing types such as manual testing, unit testing, integration testing, system testing, and automation basics. The course also covers bug reporting, test case design, test-driven development (TDD), and best practices to ensure high-quality software. By the end, learners will be able to plan, design, and execute tests effectively to deliver reliable applications.

fields.title: Foundations of Software Quality Assurance
fields.description: This course introduces the core concepts of software quality assurance and testing. Learners will explore testing strategies, defect tracking, automation frameworks, and quality metrics. Emphasis is placed on practical testing techniques, including writing effective test cases, applying black-box and white-box testing methods, and using modern testing tools. By the end of the course, participants will gain the skills to ensure software reliability, maintainability, and performance in real-world projects.

fields.title: Python Programming for Beginners
fields.description: Learn the fundamentals of Python programming, from variables and loops to functions and data structures. This course equips you with the skills to write clean, efficient code and lays the foundation for web development, data analysis, and automation projects.

fields.title: Data Structures and Algorithms in Python
fields.description: Understand the core data structures and algorithmic techniques in Python. This course covers arrays, linked lists, stacks, queues, trees, sorting, and searching algorithms, preparing you for coding interviews and real-world problem solving.

fields.title: Introduction to Machine Learning
fields.description: Explore the world of machine learning, from basic concepts to implementing predictive models. Topics include supervised and unsupervised learning, data preprocessing, model evaluation, and Python libraries like scikit-learn. Gain hands-on experience building intelligent systems.

fields.title: AI
fields.description: Learn AI, ML, Deep Learning etc

fields.title: Django REST Framework (DRF) � Build APIs with Python
fields.description: This course teaches you how to build robust and scalable RESTful APIs using Django REST Framework (DRF). You will start with the basics of API development, including serialization, views, and URL routing, and progress to advanced topics like authentication, permissions, and token-based security. By the end of the course, you�ll be able to create fully functional APIs that can power web and mobile applications, integrating seamlessly with frontend frameworks like React, Angular, or Flutter.

fields.title: Lesson 1: Introduction to Software Quality Assurance
fields.content: Understand the role of QA in software development. Learn about the importance of software quality, QA vs. testing, and the software development lifecycle (SDLC).

fields.title: Lesson 2: Fundamentals of Software Testing
fields.content: Explore the basics of software testing, including testing objectives, types of testing (manual, automated, unit, integration, system), and the testing process.

fields.title: Lesson 3: Test Planning and Design
fields.content: Learn how to create effective test plans and test cases. Topics include test strategies, test design techniques, and defining test objectives.

fields.title: Lesson 4: Defect Management
fields.content: Understand bug tracking and reporting, the defect life cycle, and tools used to manage software defects efficiently.

fields.title: Lesson 5: Testing Tools and Automation Basics
fields.content: Introduction to testing tools and frameworks. Learn automation basics, popular tools (like Selenium), and when to apply automation versus manual testing.
